      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "15 to 30 cm of snow, and even more in some localities, will fall until the early morning. The sometimes strong wind will transport the new snow. Fresh wind slabs will form adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls. They will be deposited on the unfavourable surface of an old snowpack on shady slopes. <br/> <br/> Avalanche prone weak layers exist in the bottom section of the snowpack on west, north and east facing slopes. This applies above approximately 2000 m. <br/> <br/> Below approximately 2000 m and steep sunny slopes: The old snowpack will be moist."
      },
